_:norman				    a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "norman";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "norman";
                    too:hasTitle        "<a href=\"http://www.jnd.org/\">donald norman<a>";
                    too:hasNodeSummary

"""
early on i read
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Design_of_Everyday_Things\">the design of everyday things</a>
in which norman describes some aspects good design, and where i learned the word
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Affordance\">affordance</a>.
he also talks about why many products are poorly designed.
in a more recent design
<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RlQEoJaLQRA\">ted talk</a>
he underscores the utility of beauty, and importance of factoring emotion into design.
""".

_:dawkins				    a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "dawkins";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "dawkins";
                    too:hasTitle         "<a href=\"http://richarddawkins.net/\">richard dawkins<a>";
                    too:hasNodeSummary

"""
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Selfish_Gene\">the selfish gene</a>
was a seminal book on evolution, from which we get the word
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meme\">meme</a>.
it left me with an end-to-end understanding of the rise of life on earth.
dawkins is also an outspoken
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atheist\">atheist</a>,
and proponent of
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rationalism\">rationalism</a>.
""".

_:pinker				    a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "pinker";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "pinker";
                    too:hasTitle         "<a href=\"http://stevenpinker.com/biocv\">stephen pinker<a>";
                    too:hasNodeSummary

"""
i started with
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Language_Instinct\">the language instinct</a>
which posits that humans are born with an innate capacity to develop gramatical language.
here is a facinating
<a href=\"http://comment.rsablogs.org.uk/videos/\">rsa animate</a>
<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3-son3EJTrU\">talk</a>
he gave on language and behavior.
i'm currently reading
<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Better_Angels_of_Our_Nature\">the better angels of our nature</a>
which, despite its gruesome descriptions of violence present and past, leaves me optomistic about mankind's future.
""".

